metadata:

hadiths[56]{hadithnumber,arabic,bengali,english,french,indonesian,russian,urdu,grades,reference,international_number,narrator_chain,chapter_intro}:
{"hadithnumber": "1811", "arabic": "[1811] عَنْ عَبْدِ اللّٰہِ بْنِ عُمَرَ، أَ نَّہُ قَالَ: قَدِمَ رَجُلَانِ مِنَ الْمَشْرِقِ فَخَطَبَا", "bengali": "", "english": "Malik related to me from Abdullah ibn Dinar from Abdullah ibn Umar that the Messenger of Allah, may Allah bless him and grant him peace, said, \"If a man says to his muslim brother, 'O kafir!' it is true about one of them", "french": "", "indonesian": "", "russian": "", "urdu": "حضرت عبداللہ بن عمر رضی اللہ عنہما سے روایت ہے کہ بلاشبہ مشرق کی جانب ( عراق ) سے دو شخص ( مدینہ منو", "grades": "{'name': 'Salim al-Hilali', 'grade': 'Sahih'}", "reference": "Book 56, Hadith 1", "international_number": "1811", "narrator_chain": "", "chapter_intro": "Speech"}
{"hadithnumber": "1812", "arabic": "[1812] عَنْ مَالِکٍ، أَ نَّہُ بَلَغَہُ : أَنَّ عِیسَی ابْنَ مَرْیَمَ کَانَ یَقُولُ : لَا تُکْثِرُو", "bengali": "", "english": "Malik related to me from Suhayl ibn Abu Salih from his father from Abu Hurayra that the Messenger of Allah, may Allah bless him and grant him peace, said, \"When you hear a man say, 'The people are ruined,' he himself is the most ruined of them all", "french": "", "indonesian": "", "russian": "", "urdu": "امام مالک رحمہ اللہ کو یہ خبر پہنچی کہ بے شک حضرت عیسی ابن مریم علیہم السلام فرمایا کرتے تھے : ذکر ا", "grades": "{'name': 'Salim al-Hilali', 'grade': 'Sahih'}", "reference": "Book 56, Hadith 2", "international_number": "1812", "narrator_chain": "", "chapter_intro": "Speech"}
{"hadithnumber": "1813", "arabic": "[1813] عَنْ مَالِکٍ، أَ نَّہُ بَلَغَہُ : أَنَّ عَائِشَۃَ زَوْجَ النَّبِیِّ  ﷺ  کَانَتْ تُرْسِلُ إِ", "bengali": "", "english": "Malik related to me from Abu'z-Zinad from al-Araj from Abu Hurayra that the Messenger of Allah, may Allah bless him and grant him peace, said, \"Let none of you complain about time, for Allah is time", "french": "", "indonesian": "", "russian": "", "urdu": "امام مالک رحمہ اللہ کو یہ خبر پہنچی کہ بے شک سیدہ عائشہ رضی اللہ عنہا زوجہ پیغمبر ﷺ عشاء کے بعد اپنے", "grades": "{'name': 'Salim al-Hilali', 'grade': 'Sahih'}", "reference": "Book 56, Hadith 3", "international_number": "1813", "narrator_chain": "", "chapter_intro": "Speech"}
{"hadithnumber": "1814", "arabic": "[1814] عَنِ الْمُطَّلِبَ بْنَ عَبْدِ اللّٰہِ بْنِ حَنْطَبَ الْمَخْزُومِیَّ أَخْبَرَہُ، أَنَّ رَجُل", "bengali": "", "english": "Malik related to me from Yahya ibn Said that Isa ibn Maryam encountered a pig on the road. He said to it, \"Go in peace.\" Somebody asked, \"Do you say this to a pig?\" Isa said, \"I fear lest I accustom my tongue to evil speech", "french": "", "indonesian": "", "russian": "", "urdu": "مطلب بن عبداللہ بن حنطب مخزومی رحمہ اللہ سے روایت ہے کہ ایک آدمی نے رسول اللہ ﷺ سے سوال کیا کہ غیبت", "grades": "{'name': 'Salim al-Hilali', 'grade': 'Maqtu Sahih'}", "reference": "Book 56, Hadith 4", "international_number": "1814", "narrator_chain": "", "chapter_intro": "Speech"}
{"hadithnumber": "1815", "arabic": "[1815] عَنْ عَطَائِ بْنِ یَسَارٍ : أَنَّ رَسُولَ اللّٰہِ  ﷺ  قَالَ : مَنْ وَقَاہُ اللّٰہُ شَرَّ اثْ", "bengali": "", "english": "Malik related to me from Muhammad ibn Amr ibn Alqama from his father from Bilal ibn al-Harith al-Muzani that the Messenger of Allah, may Allah bless him and grant him peace, said, \"A man speaks what is pleasing to Allah and he does not suspect that it will have the result that it does, and Allah will write for him His good pleasure for it until the day when he meets Him. And a man speaks what excites the wrath of Allah and he does not suspect that it will have the result that it does, and Allah will write His wrath for him for it until the day when he meets Him", "french": "", "indonesian": "", "russian": "", "urdu": "عطاء بن یسار رحمہ اللہ سے روایت ہے کہ بے شک رسول اللہ ﷺ نے فرمایا :’’ جس شخص کو اللہ تعالیٰ دو چیزوں", "grades": "{'name': 'Salim al-Hilali', 'grade': 'Sahih'}", "reference": "Book 56, Hadith 5", "international_number": "1815", "narrator_chain": "", "chapter_intro": "Speech"}
{"hadithnumber": "1816", "arabic": "[1816] عَنْ زَیْدِ بْنِ أَسْلَمَ، عَنْ أَبِیہِ، أَنَّ عُمَرَ بْنَ الْخَطَّابِ دَخَلَ عَلَی أبِی", "bengali": "", "english": "Malik related to me from Abdullah ibn Dinar that Abu Salih as- Samman informed him that Abu Hurayra said, \"Truly a man utters words to which he attaches no importance, and by them he falls into the fire of Jahannam, and truly a man utters words to which he attaches no importance, and by them Allah raises him into the Garden", "french": "", "indonesian": "", "russian": "", "urdu": "زید بن اسلم رحمہ اللہ اپنے والد ( اسلم رحمہ اللہ جو حضرت عمر رضی اللہ عنہ کے آزاد کردہ غلام تھے ) سے", "grades": "{'name': 'Salim al-Hilali', 'grade': 'Mauquf Sahih'}", "reference": "Book 56, Hadith 6", "international_number": "1816", "narrator_chain": "", "chapter_intro": "Speech"}
{"hadithnumber": "1817", "arabic": "[1817] عَنْ عَبْدِ اللّٰہِ بْنِ دِینَارٍ، قَالَ : کُنْتُ أَنَا وَعَبْدُ اللّٰہِ بْنُ عُمَرَ عِنْدَ", "bengali": "", "english": "Malik related to me from Zayd ibn Aslam that Abdullah ibn Umar said, \"Two men from the east stood up and spoke, and people were amazed at their eloquence. The Messenger of Allah, may Allah bless him and grant him peace, said, 'Some eloquence is sorcery,' or he said, 'Part of eloquence is sorcery", "french": "", "indonesian": "", "russian": "", "urdu": "عبداللہ بن دینار رحمہ اللہ سے روایت ہے ، کہتے ہیں : میں اور حضرت عبداللہ بن عمر رضی اللہ عنہما ، حضر", "grades": "{'name': 'Salim al-Hilali', 'grade': 'Sahih'}", "reference": "Book 56, Hadith 7", "international_number": "1817", "narrator_chain": "", "chapter_intro": "Speech"}
{"hadithnumber": "1818", "arabic": "[1818] عَنْ عَبْدِ اللّٰہِ بْنِ عُمَرَ : أَنَّ رَسُولَ اللّٰہِ  ﷺ  قَالَ : إِذَا کَانَ ثَـلَاثَۃٌ ف", "bengali": "", "english": "Malik related to me that he heard that Isa ibn Maryam used to say, \"Do not speak much without the mention of Allah for you will harden your hearts. A hard heart is far from Allah, but you do not know. Do not look at the wrong actions of people as if you were lords. Look at your wrong actions as if you were slaves. Some people are afflicted by wrong action and some people are protected from it. Be merciful to the people of affliction and praise Allah for His protection", "french": "", "indonesian": "", "russian": "", "urdu": "حضرت عبداللہ بن عمر رضی اللہ عنہما سے روایت ہے کہ بلاشبہ رسول اللہ ﷺ نے فرمایا :’’ جب ( کسی جگہ ) تی", "grades": "{'name': 'Salim al-Hilali', 'grade': 'Maqtu Daif'}", "reference": "Book 56, Hadith 8", "international_number": "1818", "narrator_chain": "", "chapter_intro": "Speech"}
{"hadithnumber": "1819", "arabic": "[1819] عَنْ صَفْوَانَ بْنِ سُلَیْمٍ، أَنَّ رَجُلاً قَالَ لِرَسُولِ اللّٰہِ  ﷺ : أَکْذِبُ امْرَأَت", "bengali": "", "english": "Malik related to me that he heard that A'isha, the wife of the Prophet, may Allah bless him and grant him peace, sent a message to one of her family after the evening prayer, saying, \"Will you not allow the recording angel to rest?", "french": "", "indonesian": "", "russian": "", "urdu": "صفوان بن سلیم رحمہ اللہ سے روایت ہے کہ ایک آدمی نے رسول اللہ ﷺ سے عرض کیا : کیا میں اپنی بیوی سے جھو", "grades": "{'name': 'Salim al-Hilali', 'grade': 'Mauquf Daif'}", "reference": "Book 56, Hadith 9", "international_number": "1819", "narrator_chain": "", "chapter_intro": "Speech"}
{"hadithnumber": "1820", "arabic": "[1820] عَنْ مَالِکٍ، أَ نَّہُ بَلَغَہُ، أَنَّ عَبْدَ اللّٰہِ بْنَ مَسْعُودٍ کَانَ یَقُولُ : عَلَیْ", "bengali": "", "english": "Malik related to me from al-Walid ibn Abdullah ibn Sayyad that al-Muttalib ibn Abdullah ibn Hantab al-Makhzumi informed him that a man asked the Messenger of Allah, may Allah bless him and grant him peace, \"What is backbiting?\" The Messenger of Allah, may Allah bless him and grant him peace, said, \"It is to mention about a man what he does not want to hear.\" He said, \"Messenger of Allah! Even if it is true?\" The Messenger of Allah, may Allah bless him and grant him peace, said, \"If you utter something false, then it is slander", "french": "", "indonesian": "", "russian": "", "urdu": "امام مالک رحمہ اللہ کو یہ خبر پہنچی کہ حضرت عبداللہ بن مسعود رضی اللہ عنہ فرمایا کرتے تھے :’’ سچ کو", "grades": "{'name': 'Salim al-Hilali', 'grade': 'Sahih Lighairihi'}", "reference": "Book 56, Hadith 10", "international_number": "1820", "narrator_chain": "", "chapter_intro": "Speech"}
{"hadithnumber": "1821", "arabic": "[1821] عَنْ مَالِکٍ، أَ نَّہُ بَلَغَہُ : أَ نَّہُ قِیلَ لِلُقْمَانَ : مَا بَلَغَ بِکَ مَا نَرَی ؟", "bengali": "", "english": "Malik related to me from Zayd ibn Aslam from Ata ibn Yasar that the Messenger of Allah, may Allah bless him and grant him peace, said, \"Whomever Allah protects from the evil of two things will enter the Garden.\" A man said, \"Messenger of Allah, do not tell us!\" The Messenger of Allah, may Allah bless him and grant him peace, was silent. Then the Messenger of Allah, may Allah bless him and grant him peace, repeated what he had said the first time. The man said to him, \"Do not tell us, Messenger of Allah!\" The Messenger of Allah, may Allah bless him and grant him peace, was silent. Then the Messenger of Allah, may Allah bless him and grant him peace, said the same thing again. The man said, \"Do not tell us, Messenger of Allah!\" Then the Messenger of Allah, may Allah bless him and grant him peace, said the same thing again. Then the man began to say what he had said previously and a man at his side silenced him. The Messenger of Allah, may Allah bless him and grant him peace, said, \"Whomever Allah protects from the evil of two things will enter the Garden. They are what is between his jaws and what is between his legs, what is between his jaws and what is between his legs, what is between his jaws and what is between his legs", "french": "", "indonesian": "", "russian": "", "urdu": "امام مالک رحمہ اللہ کو یہ خبر پہنچی کہ لقمان حکیم سے کہا گیا : آپ کو اس مقام تک کس چیز نے پہنچایا ہے", "grades": "{'name': 'Salim al-Hilali', 'grade': 'Daif'}", "reference": "Book 56, Hadith 11", "international_number": "1821", "narrator_chain": "", "chapter_intro": "Speech"}
{"hadithnumber": "1822", "arabic": "[1822] عَنْ مَالِکٍ، أَ نَّہُ بَلَغَہُ، أَنَّ عَبْدَ اللّٰہِ بْنَ مَسْعُودٍ کَانَ یَقُولُ : لَا یَ", "bengali": "", "english": "Malik related to me from Zayd ibn Aslam from his father that Umar ibn al-Khattab came upon Abu Bakr as-Siddiq pulling his tongue. Umar said to him, \"Stop, may Allah forgive you!\" Abu Bakr replied, \"This has brought me to dangerous places", "french": "", "indonesian": "", "russian": "", "urdu": "امام مالک رحمہ اللہ کو یہ خبر پہنچی کہ حضرت عبداللہ بن مسعود رضی اللہ عنہ فرمایا کرتے تھے : آدمی مسل", "grades": "{'name': 'Salim al-Hilali', 'grade': 'Mauquf Sahih'}", "reference": "Book 56, Hadith 12", "international_number": "1822", "narrator_chain": "", "chapter_intro": "Speech"}
{"hadithnumber": "1823", "arabic": "[1823] عَنْ صَفْوَانَ بْنِ سُلَیْمٍ، أَ نَّہُ قَالَ : قِیلَ لِرَسُولِ اللّٰہِ  ﷺ  : أَیَکُونُ الْم", "bengali": "", "english": "Malik related to me from Abdullah ibn Dinar saying, \"Abdullah ibn Umar and I were at the house of Khalid ibn Uqba who was away at the market. A man came who wanted to speak to Abdullah ibn Umar and I was the only other person present Abdullah ibn Umar called another man so that we were four and said to me and the man whom he had called, 'Go a little way off together, because I heard the Messenger of Allah, may Allah bless him and grant him peace, say, \"Two do not converse secretly to the exclusion of another", "french": "", "indonesian": "", "russian": "", "urdu": "صفوان بن سلیم رحمہ اللہ سے روایت ہے ، کہتے ہیں کہ رسول اللہ ﷺ سے کہا گیا : کیا مومن بزدل ہو سکتا ہے", "grades": "{'name': 'Salim al-Hilali', 'grade': 'Sahih'}", "reference": "Book 56, Hadith 13", "international_number": "1823", "narrator_chain": "", "chapter_intro": "Speech"}
{"hadithnumber": "1824", "arabic": "[1824] عَنْ أبِی ہُرَیْرَۃَأَنَّ رَسُولَ اللّٰہِ  ﷺ  قَالَ : إِنَّ اللّٰہَ یَرْضَی لَکُمْ ثَلَاثاً", "bengali": "", "english": "Malik related to me from Nafi from Abdullah ibn Umar that the Messenger of Allah, may Allah bless him and grant him peace, said, \"Two must not converse secretly to the exclusion of another person", "french": "", "indonesian": "", "russian": "", "urdu": "حضرت ابوہریرہ رضی اللہ عنہ سے روایت ہے کہ بلاشبہ رسول اللہ ﷺ نے فرمایا :’’ یقیناً اللہ تعالیٰ تمھارے", "grades": "{'name': 'Salim al-Hilali', 'grade': 'Sahih'}", "reference": "Book 56, Hadith 14", "international_number": "1824", "narrator_chain": "", "chapter_intro": "Speech"}
{"hadithnumber": "1825", "arabic": "[1825] عَنْ أبِی ہُرَیْرَۃَ، أَنَّ رَسُولَ اللّٰہِ  ﷺ  قَالَ : مِنْ شَرِّ النَّاسِ ذُو الْوَجْہَیْ", "bengali": "", "english": "Malik related to me from Safwan ibn Sulaym that a man asked the Messenger of Allah, may Allah bless him and grant him peace, \"Can I lie to my wife, Messenger of Allah?\" The Messenger of Allah, may Allah bless him and grant him peace, said, \"There is no good in lying.\" The man said, \"Messenger of Allah! Shall I make her a promise and tell her?\" The Messenger of Allah, may Allah bless him and grant him peace, said, \"It will not be held against you", "french": "", "indonesian": "", "russian": "", "urdu": "حضرت ابوہریرہ رضی اللہ عنہ سے روایت ہے کہ یقیناً رسول اللہ ﷺ نے فرمایا :’’ بدترین لوگوں میں سے دو چہ", "grades": "{'name': 'Salim al-Hilali', 'grade': 'Daif'}", "reference": "Book 56, Hadith 15", "international_number": "1825", "narrator_chain": "", "chapter_intro": "Speech"}
{"hadithnumber": "1826", "arabic": "[1826] عَنْ مَالِکٍ، أَ نَّہُ بَلَغَہُ، أَنَّ أُمَّ سَلَمَۃَ زَوْجَ النَّبِیِّ  ﷺ  قَالَتْ : یَا", "bengali": "", "english": "Malik related to me that he heard that Abdullah ibn Masud used to say, \"You must tell the truth. Truthfulness leads to right action. Right action leads to the Garden. Beware of lying. Lying leads to corruption, and corruption leads to the Fire. Don't you see that it is said, 'He speaks the truth and acts rightly,' and, 'He lies and is corrupt", "french": "", "indonesian": "", "russian": "", "urdu": "امام مالک رحمہ اللہ کو یہ خبر پہنچی کہ بے شک سیدہ ام سلمہ رضی اللہ عنہا زوجہ پیغمبر ﷺ نے عرض کیا کہ", "grades": "{'name': 'Salim al-Hilali', 'grade': 'Mauquf Daif'}", "reference": "Book 56, Hadith 16", "international_number": "1826", "narrator_chain": "", "chapter_intro": "Speech"}
{"hadithnumber": "1827", "arabic": "[1827] عَنْ عُمَرَ بْنَ عَبْدِ الْعَزِیزِ یَقُولُ : کَانَ یُقَالُ إِنَّ اللّٰہَ تَبَارَکَ وَتَعَالَی", "bengali": "", "english": "Malik related to me that he heard that someone said to Luqman, \"What has brought you to what we see?\" meaning his high rank. Luqman said, \"Truthful speech, fulfilling the trust, and leaving what does not concern me", "french": "", "indonesian": "", "russian": "", "urdu": "حضرت عمر بن عبدالعزیز رحمہ اللہ سے روایت ہے ، فرماتے ہیں : یہ تو کہا جاتا ہے کہ بے شک اللہ تبارک و ت", "grades": "{'name': 'Salim al-Hilali', 'grade': 'Maqtu Sahih Lighairihi'}", "reference": "Book 56, Hadith 17", "international_number": "1827", "narrator_chain": "", "chapter_intro": "Speech"}
{"hadithnumber": "1828", "arabic": "[1828] عَنْ مَالِکٍ، عَنْ إِسْحَاقَ بْنِ عَبْدِ اللّٰہِ بْنِ أبِی طَلْحَۃَ، عَنْ أَنَسِ بْنِ مَالِ", "bengali": "", "english": "Malik related to me that he heard that Abdullah ibn Masud used to say, \"The slave continues to lie and a black spot grows in his heart until all his heart becomes black. Then he is written, in Allah's sight, among the liars", "french": "", "indonesian": "", "russian": "", "urdu": "حضرت انس بن مالک رضی اللہ عنہ سے روایت ہے ، کہتے ہیں کہ میں نے حضرت عمر بن خطاب رضی اللہ عنہ کو سنا", "grades": "{'name': 'Salim al-Hilali', 'grade': 'Mauquf Daif'}", "reference": "Book 56, Hadith 18", "international_number": "1828", "narrator_chain": "", "chapter_intro": "Speech"}
{"hadithnumber": "1829", "arabic": "[1829] عَنِ الْقَاسِمَ بْنَ مُحَمَّدٍ کَانَ یَقُولُ : أَدْرَکْتُ النَّاسَ وَمَا یَعْجَبُونَ بِالْقَ", "bengali": "", "english": "Malik related to me that Safwan ibn Sulaym said, \"The Messenger of Allah, may Allah bless him and grant him peace, was asked, 'Can the mumin be a coward?' He said, 'Yes.' He was asked, 'Can the mumin be a miser?' He said, 'Yes.' He was asked, 'Can the mumin be a liar?' He said, 'No", "french": "", "indonesian": "", "russian": "", "urdu": "قاسم بن محمد رحمہ اللہ ( بن ابی بکر صدیق رضی اللہ عنہ ) سے روایت ہے ، وہ فرمایا کرتے تھے : میں نے لو", "grades": "{'name': 'Salim al-Hilali', 'grade': 'Daif'}", "reference": "Book 56, Hadith 19", "international_number": "1829", "narrator_chain": "", "chapter_intro": "Speech"}
{"hadithnumber": "1830", "arabic": "[1830] عَنْ عَامِرِ بْنِ عَبْدِ اللّٰہِ بْنِ الزُّبَیْرِ، أَنَّہُ کَانَ إِذَا سَمِعَ الرَّعْدَ تَرَ", "bengali": "", "english": "Malik related to me from Suhayl ibn Abi Salih from his father from Abu Hurayra that the Messenger of Allah, may Allah bless him and grant him peace, said, \"Allah is pleased with three things from you, and He is angry with three things from you. He is pleased that you worship Him and do not associate anything with Him, and that you take hold of the rope of Allah altogether, and that you give good counsel to the one to whom Allah gives command over you. He is angry with you for gossip, squandering property, and asking too many questions", "french": "", "indonesian": "", "russian": "", "urdu": "عامر بن عبداللہ بن زبیر رحمہ اللہ سے روایت ہے کہ جب وہ کڑک کی آواز سنتے تو گفتگو چھوڑ دیتے اور فرمات", "grades": "{'name': 'Salim al-Hilali', 'grade': 'Sahih'}", "reference": "Book 56, Hadith 20", "international_number": "1830", "narrator_chain": "", "chapter_intro": "Speech"}
{"hadithnumber": "1831", "arabic": "[1831] عَنْ عَائِشَۃَ أُمِّ الْمُؤْمِنِینَ : أَنَّ أَزْوَاجَ النَّبِیِّ  ﷺ  حِینَ تُوفِّی رَسُول", "bengali": "", "english": "Malik related to me from Abu'z-Zinad from al-Araj from Abu Hurayra that the Messenger of Allah, may Allah bless him and grant him peace, said, \"One of the most evil of people is the two-faced person who shows one face to these people and another face to those people", "french": "", "indonesian": "", "russian": "", "urdu": "سیدہ عائشہ ام المومنین رضی اللہ عنہا سے روایت ہے کہ بلاشبہ نبی کریم ﷺ کی ازواج مطہرات نے جس وقت کہ ر", "grades": "{'name': 'Salim al-Hilali', 'grade': 'Sahih'}", "reference": "Book 56, Hadith 21", "international_number": "1831", "narrator_chain": "", "chapter_intro": "Speech"}
{"hadithnumber": "1832", "arabic": "[1832] عَنْ أبِی ہُرَیْرَۃَ، أَنَّ رَسُولَ اللّٰہِ  ﷺ  قَالَ : لَا یَقْتَسِمُ وَرَثَتِی دَنَانِیرَ", "bengali": "", "english": "Malik related to me that he had heard that Umm Salama, the wife of the Prophet, may Allah bless him and grant him peace, said, \"Messenger of Allah! Shall we be destroyed while there are people who are salih among us?\" The Messenger of Allah, may Allah bless him and grant him peace, said, \"Yes, if there is much wickedness", "french": "", "indonesian": "", "russian": "", "urdu": "حضرت ابوہریرہ رضی اللہ عنہ سے روایت ہے کہ بلاشبہ رسول اللہ ﷺ نے فرمایا :’’ میرے ورثاء دینار تقسیم نہ", "grades": "{'name': 'Salim al-Hilali', 'grade': 'Sahih Lighairihi'}", "reference": "Book 56, Hadith 22", "international_number": "1832", "narrator_chain": "", "chapter_intro": "Speech"}
{"hadithnumber": "1833", "arabic": "[1833] عَنْ أبِی ہُرَیْرَۃَ، أَنَّ رَسُولَ اللّٰہِ  ﷺ  قَالَ : نَارُ بَنِی آدَمَ الَّتِی یُوقِدُو", "bengali": "", "english": "Malik related to me that Ismail ibn Abi Hakim heard Umar ibn Abd al-Aziz say, \"Some say that Allah the Blessed, the Exalted, will not punish the many for the wrong action of the few. However, when the objectionable action is committed openly, then they all deserve to be punished", "french": "", "indonesian": "", "russian": "", "urdu": "حضرت ابوہریرہ رضی اللہ عنہ سے روایت ہے کہ بلاشبہ رسول اللہ ﷺ نے فرمایا :’’ بنو آدم کی وہ آگ جسے وہ ج", "grades": "{'name': 'Salim al-Hilali', 'grade': 'Maqtu Sahih'}", "reference": "Book 56, Hadith 23", "international_number": "1833", "narrator_chain": "", "chapter_intro": "Speech"}
{"hadithnumber": "1834", "arabic": "[1834] عَنْ أبِی ہُرَیْرَۃَ، أَنَّہُ قَالَ : أَتُرَوْنَہَا حَمْرَائَ کَنَارِکُمْ ہَذِہِ، لَہِیَ ا", "bengali": "", "english": "Malik related to me from Ishaq ibn Abdullah ibn Abi Talha that Anas ibn Malik said, \"I heard Umar ibn al-Khattab, when I was going out with him to visit an orchard, say to himself, and there was a wall between him and me and he was inside the garden, 'Umar ibn al-Khattab, amir al-muminin! Well done! Well done! By Allah, fear Allah or he will punish you", "french": "", "indonesian": "", "russian": "", "urdu": "حضرت ابوہریرہ رضی اللہ عنہ سے روایت ہے ، انھوں نے فرمایا :’’ کیا تم اس ( جہنم کی آگ ) کو سرخ سمجھتے", "grades": "{'name': 'Salim al-Hilali', 'grade': 'Mauquf Sahih'}", "reference": "Book 56, Hadith 24", "international_number": "1834", "narrator_chain": "", "chapter_intro": "Speech"}
{"hadithnumber": "1835", "arabic": "[1835] عَنْ أبِی الْحُبَابِ سَعِیدِ بْنِ یَسَارٍ، أَنَّ رَسُولَ اللّٰہِ  ﷺ  قَالَ : مَنْ تَصَدَّقَ", "bengali": "", "english": "Malik said, \"I heard that al-Qasim ibn Muhammad used to say, 'I have seen the people, (i.e. the companions), and they were not impressed by speech.' \" Malik said, \"He meant that only action and deeds would be looked at, not words", "french": "", "indonesian": "", "russian": "", "urdu": "ابوالحباب سعید بن یسار رحمہ اللہ سے روایت ہے کہ بلاشبہ رسول اللہ ﷺ نے فرمایا :’’ جس شخص نے پاکیزہ (", "grades": "{'name': 'Salim al-Hilali', 'grade': 'Maqtu Hasan'}", "reference": "Book 56, Hadith 25", "international_number": "1835", "narrator_chain": "", "chapter_intro": "Speech"}
{"hadithnumber": "1836", "arabic": "[1836] اَنَّ أَنَسَ بْنَ مَالِکٍ یَقُولُ : کَانَ أَبُوطَلْحَۃَ أَکْثَرَ أَنْصَارِیٍّ بِالْمَدِین", "bengali": "", "english": "Malik related to me that Amir ibn Abdullah ibn az-Zubayr would stop speaking when he heard thunder and say, \"Glory be to Allah whom the thunder glorifies with His praise and the angels from the fear of Him.\" (Subhana-aladhee yusabihu ar-radu bi hamdihi wa mala'ikatu min khiyfatihi.) Then he would say, \"This is a severe warning to the people of the earth", "french": "", "indonesian": "", "russian": "", "urdu": "حضرت انس بن مالک رضی اللہ عنہ سے روایت ہے ، کہتے ہیں : ( ان کے سوتیلے والد ) حضرت ابوطلحہ رضی اللہ ع", "grades": "{'name': 'Salim al-Hilali', 'grade': 'Mauquf Sahih'}", "reference": "Book 56, Hadith 26", "international_number": "1836", "narrator_chain": "", "chapter_intro": "Speech"}
{"hadithnumber": "1837", "arabic": "[1837] عَنْ زَیْدِ بْنِ أَسْلَمَ، أَنَّ رَسُولَ اللّٰہِ  ﷺ  قَالَ : أَعْطُوا السَّائِلَ وَإِنْ جَ", "bengali": "", "english": "Malik related to me from Ibn Shihab from Urwa ibn az-Zubayr from A'isha, umm al-muminin that when the Messenger of Allah, may Allah bless him and grant him peace, died, the wives of the Prophet, may Allah bless him and grant him peace, wanted to send Uthman ibn Affan to Abu Bakr as-Siddiq to ask him about their inheritance from the Messenger of Allah, may Allah bless him and grant him peace A'isha said to them, \"Didn't the Messenger of Allah, may Allah bless him and grant him peace, say, 'No one inherits from us. What we leave is sadaqa", "french": "", "indonesian": "", "russian": "", "urdu": "زید بن اسلم رحمہ اللہ سے روایت ہے کہ بلاشبہ رسول اللہ ﷺ نے فرمایا :’’ سائل ( مانگنے والے ) کو دیا کر", "grades": "{'name': 'Salim al-Hilali', 'grade': 'Sahih'}", "reference": "Book 56, Hadith 27", "international_number": "1837", "narrator_chain": "", "chapter_intro": "Speech"}
{"hadithnumber": "1838", "arabic": "[1838] عَنْ عَمْرِو بْنِ مُعَاذٍ الأَشْہَلِیِّ الْأَنْصَاری، عَنْ جَدَّتِہِ أَ نَّہَا قَالَتْ : ق", "bengali": "", "english": "Malik related to me from Abu'z-Zinad from al-Araj from Abu Hurayra that the Messenger of Allah, may Allah bless him and grant him peace, said, \"My inheritance is not divided up by the dinar. What I leave apart from the maintenance of my wives and provision for my servant is sadaqa", "french": "", "indonesian": "", "russian": "", "urdu": "عمرو بن معاذ ( بن سعد بن معاذ ) اشہلی انصاری رحمہ اللہ نے اپنی دادی ( حواء بنت یزید بن سکن رحمۃ اللہ", "grades": "{'name': 'Salim al-Hilali', 'grade': 'Sahih'}", "reference": "Book 56, Hadith 28", "international_number": "1838", "narrator_chain": "", "chapter_intro": "Speech"}
{"hadithnumber": "1938", "arabic": "حَدَّثَنِي مَالِكٌ، عَنْ عَبْدِ اللَّهِ بْنِ دِينَارٍ، عَنْ عَبْدِ اللَّهِ بْنِ عُمَرَ، أَنَّ رَسُولَ اللَّهِ صلى الله عليه وسلم قَالَ ‏ ‏ مَنْ قَالَ لأَخِيهِ يَا كَافِرُ ‏.‏ فَقَدْ بَاءَ بِهَا أَحَدُهُمَا ‏\"\"‏ ‏.‏\"", "bengali": "", "english": "Malik related to me from Abdullah ibn Dinar from Abdullah ibn Umar that the Messenger of Allah, may Allah bless him and grant him peace, said, \"If a man says to his muslim brother, 'O kafir!' it is true about one of them.\"", "french": "", "indonesian": "", "russian": "", "urdu": "", "grades": "", "reference": "", "international_number": "", "narrator_chain": "", "chapter_intro": "Speech"}
{"hadithnumber": "1939", "arabic": "وَحَدَّثَنِي مَالِكٌ، عَنْ سُهَيْلِ بْنِ أَبِي صَالِحٍ، عَنْ أَبِيهِ، عَنْ أَبِي هُرَيْرَةَ، أَنَّ رَسُولَ اللَّهِ صلى الله عليه وسلم قَالَ ‏ ‏ إِذَا سَمِعْتَ الرَّجُلَ يَقُولُ هَلَكَ النَّاسُ ‏.‏ فَهُوَ أَهْلَكُهُمْ ‏\"\"‏ ‏.‏\"", "bengali": "", "english": "Malik related to me from Suhayl ibn Abu Salih from his father from Abu Hurayra that the Messenger of Allah, may Allah bless him and grant him peace, said, \"When you hear a man say, 'The people are ruined,' he himself is the most ruined of them all.\"", "french": "", "indonesian": "", "russian": "", "urdu": "", "grades": "", "reference": "", "international_number": "", "narrator_chain": "", "chapter_intro": "Speech"}
{"hadithnumber": "1940", "arabic": "وَحَدَّثَنِي مَالِكٌ، عَنْ أَبِي الزِّنَادِ، عَنِ الأَعْرَجِ، عَنْ أَبِي هُرَيْرَةَ، أَنَّ رَسُولَ اللَّهِ صلى الله عليه وسلم قَالَ ‏ ‏ لاَ يَقُلْ أَحَدُكُمْ يَا خَيْبَةَ الدَّهْرِ ‏.‏ فَإِنَّ اللَّهَ هُوَ الدَّهْرُ ‏\"\"‏ ‏.‏\"", "bengali": "", "english": "Malik related to me from Abu'z-Zinad from al-Araj from Abu Hurayra that the Messenger of Allah, may Allah bless him and grant him peace, said, \"Let none of you complain about time, for Allah is time.'", "french": "", "indonesian": "", "russian": "", "urdu": "", "grades": "", "reference": "", "international_number": "", "narrator_chain": "", "chapter_intro": "Speech"}
{"hadithnumber": "1941", "arabic": "وَحَدَّثَنِي مَالِكٌ، عَنْ يَحْيَى بْنِ سَعِيدٍ، أَنَّ عِيسَى ابْنَ مَرْيَمَ، لَقِيَ خِنْزِيرًا بِالطَّرِيقِ فَقَالَ لَهُ انْفُذْ بِسَلاَمٍ ‏.‏ فَقِيلَ لَهُ تَقُولُ هَذَا لِخِنْزِيرٍ فَقَالَ عِيسَى إِنِّي أَخَافُ أَنْ أُعَوِّدَ لِسَانِي النُّطْقَ بِالسُّوءِ ‏.‏", "bengali": "", "english": "Malik related to me from Yahya ibn Said that Isa ibn Maryam encountered a pig on the road. He said to it, \"Go in peace.\" Somebody asked, \"Do you say this to a pig?\" Isa said, \"I fear lest I accustom my tongue to evil speech.\"", "french": "", "indonesian": "", "russian": "", "urdu": "", "grades": "", "reference": "", "international_number": "", "narrator_chain": "", "chapter_intro": "Speech"}
{"hadithnumber": "1942", "arabic": "حَدَّثَنِي مَالِكٌ، عَنْ مُحَمَّدِ بْنِ عَمْرِو بْنِ عَلْقَمَةَ، عَنْ أَبِيهِ، عَنْ بِلاَلِ بْنِ الْحَارِثِ الْمُزَنِيِّ، أَنَّ رَسُولَ اللَّهِ صلى الله عليه وسلم قَالَ ‏ ‏ إِنَّ الرَّجُلَ لَيَتَكَلَّمُ بِالْكَلِمَةِ مِنْ رِضْوَانِ اللَّهِ مَا كَانَ يَظُنُّ أَنْ تَبْلُغَ مَا بَلَغَتْ يَكْتُبُ اللَّهُ لَهُ بِهَا رِضْوَانَهُ إِلَى يَوْمِ يَلْقَاهُ وَإِنَّ الرَّجُلَ لَيَتَكَلَّمُ بِالْكَلَمِةِ مِنْ سَخَطِ اللَّهِ مَا كَانَ يَظُنُّ أَنْ تَبْلُغَ مَا بَلَغَتْ يَكْتُبُ اللَّهُ لَهُ بِهَا سَخَطَهُ إِلَى يَوْمِ يَلْقَاهُ ‏\"\"‏ ‏.‏\"", "bengali": "", "english": "Malik related to me from Muhammad ibn Amr ibn Alqama from his father from Bilal ibn al-Harith al-Muzani that the Messenger of Allah, may Allah bless him and grant him peace, said, \"A man speaks what is pleasing to Allah and he does not suspect that it will have the result that it does, and Allah will write for him His good pleasure for it until the day when he meets Him. And a man speaks what excites the wrath of Allah and he does not suspect that it will have the result that it does, and Allah will write His wrath for him for it until the day when he meets Him.\"", "french": "", "indonesian": "", "russian": "", "urdu": "", "grades": "", "reference": "", "international_number": "", "narrator_chain": "", "chapter_intro": "Speech"}
{"hadithnumber": "1943", "arabic": "وَحَدَّثَنِي مَالِكٌ، عَنْ عَبْدِ اللَّهِ بْنِ دِينَارٍ، عَنْ أَبِي صَالِحٍ السَّمَّانِ، أَنَّهُ أَخْبَرَهُ أَنَّ أَبَا هُرَيْرَةَ قَالَ إِنَّ الرَّجُلَ لَيَتَكَلَّمُ بِالْكَلِمَةِ مَا يُلْقِي لَهَا بَالاً يَهْوِي بِهَا فِي نَارِ جَهَنَّمَ وَإِنَّ الرَّجُلَ لَيَتَكَلَّمُ بِالْكَلَمَةِ مَا يُلْقِي لَهَا بَالاً يَرْفَعُهُ اللَّهُ بِهَا فِي الْجَنَّةِ ‏.‏", "bengali": "", "english": "Malik related to me from Abdullah ibn Dinar that Abu Salih as- Samman informed him that Abu Hurayra said, \"Truly a man utters words to which he attaches no importance, and by them he falls into the fire of Jahannam, and truly a man utters words to which he attaches no importance, and by them Allah raises him into the Garden.\"", "french": "", "indonesian": "", "russian": "", "urdu": "", "grades": "", "reference": "", "international_number": "", "narrator_chain": "", "chapter_intro": "Speech"}
{"hadithnumber": "1944", "arabic": "حَدَّثَنِي مَالِكٌ، عَنْ زَيْدِ بْنِ أَسْلَمَ، عَنْ عَبْدِ اللَّهِ بْنِ عُمَرَ، أَنَّهُ قَالَ قَدِمَ رَجُلاَنِ مِنَ الْمَشْرِقِ فَخَطَبَا فَعَجِبَ النَّاسُ لِبَيَانِهِمَا فَقَالَ رَسُولُ اللَّهِ صلى الله عليه وسلم ‏\"‏ إِنَّ مِنَ الْبَيَانِ لَسِحْرًا ‏\"‏ ‏.‏ أَوْ قَالَ ‏\"‏ إِنَّ بَعْضَ الْبَيَانِ لَسِحْرٌ ‏\"‏ ‏.‏", "bengali": "", "english": "Malik related to me from Zayd ibn Aslam that Abdullah ibn Umar said, \"Two men from the east stood up and spoke, and people were amazed at their eloquence. The Messenger of Allah, may Allah bless him and grant him peace, said, 'Some eloquence is sorcery,' or he said, 'Part of eloquence is sorcery.' \"", "french": "", "indonesian": "", "russian": "", "urdu": "", "grades": "", "reference": "", "international_number": "", "narrator_chain": "", "chapter_intro": "Speech"}
{"hadithnumber": "1945", "arabic": "وَحَدَّثَنِي مَالِكٌ، أَنَّهُ بَلَغَهُ أَنَّ عِيسَى ابْنَ مَرْيَمَ، كَانَ يَقُولُ لاَ تُكْثِرُوا الْكَلاَمَ بِغَيْرِ ذِكْرِ اللَّهِ فَتَقْسُوَ قُلُوبُكُمْ فَإِنَّ الْقَلْبَ الْقَاسِيَ بَعِيدٌ مِنَ اللَّهِ وَلَكِنْ لاَ تَعْلَمُونَ وَلاَ تَنْظُرُوا فِي ذُنُوبِ النَّاسِ كَأَنَّكُمْ أَرْبَابٌ وَانْظُرُوا فِي ذُنُوبِكُمْ كَأَنَّكُمْ عَبِيدٌ فَإِنَّمَا النَّاسُ مُبْتَلًى وَمُعَافًى فَارْحَمُوا أَهْلَ الْبَلاَءِ وَاحْمَدُوا اللَّهَ عَلَى الْعَافِيَةِ ‏.‏", "bengali": "", "english": "Malik related to me that he heard that Isa ibn Maryam used to say, \"Do not speak much without the mention of Allah for you will harden your hearts. A hard heart is far from Allah, but you do not know. Do not look at the wrong actions of people as if you were lords. Look at your wrong actions as if you were slaves. Some people are afflicted by wrong action and some people are protected from it. Be merciful to the people of affliction and praise Allah for His protection.\"", "french": "", "indonesian": "", "russian": "", "urdu": "", "grades": "", "reference": "", "international_number": "", "narrator_chain": "", "chapter_intro": "Speech"}
{"hadithnumber": "1946", "arabic": "وَحَدَّثَنِي مَالِكُ، أَنَّهُ بَلَغَهُ أَنَّ عَائِشَةَ، زَوْجَ النَّبِيِّ صلى الله عليه وسلم كَانَتْ تُرْسِلُ إِلَى بَعْضِ أَهْلِهَا بَعْدَ الْعَتَمَةِ فَتَقُولُ أَلاَ تُرِيحُونَ الْكُتَّابَ", "bengali": "", "english": "Malik related to me that he heard that A'isha, the wife of the Prophet, may Allah bless him and grant him peace, sent a message to one of her family after the evening prayer, saying, \"Will you not allow the recording angel to rest?\"", "french": "", "indonesian": "", "russian": "", "urdu": "", "grades": "", "reference": "", "international_number": "", "narrator_chain": "", "chapter_intro": "Speech"}
{"hadithnumber": "1947", "arabic": "حَدَّثَنِي مَالِكٌ، عَنِ الْوَلِيدِ بْنِ عَبْدِ اللَّهِ بْنِ صَيَّادٍ، أَنَّ الْمُطَّلِبَ بْنَ عَبْدِ اللَّهِ بْنِ حَنْطَبَ الْمَخْزُومِيَّ، أَخْبَرَهُ أَنَّ رَجُلاً سَأَلَ رَسُولَ اللَّهِ صلى الله عليه وسلم مَا الْغِيبَةُ فَقَالَ رَسُولُ اللَّهِ صلى الله عليه وسلم ‏\"‏ أَنْ تَذْكُرَ مِنَ الْمَرْءِ مَا يَكْرَهُ أَنْ يَسْمَعَ ‏\"‏ ‏.‏ قَالَ يَا رَسُولَ اللَّهِ وَإِنْ كَانَ حَقًّا قَالَ رَسُولُ اللَّهِ صلى الله عليه وسلم ‏\"‏ إِذَا قُلْتَ بَاطِلاً فَذَلِكَ الْبُهْتَانُ ‏\"‏ ‏.‏", "bengali": "", "english": "Malik related to me from al-Walid ibn Abdullah ibn Sayyad that al-Muttalib ibn Abdullah ibn Hantab al-Makhzumi informed him that a man asked the Messenger of Allah, may Allah bless him and grant him peace, \"What is backbiting?\" The Messenger of Allah, may Allah bless him and grant him peace, said, \"It is to mention about a man what he does not want to hear.\" He said, \"Messenger of Allah! Even if it is true?\" The Messenger of Allah, may Allah bless him and grant him peace, said, \"If you utter something false, then it is slander.\"", "french": "", "indonesian": "", "russian": "", "urdu": "", "grades": "", "reference": "", "international_number": "", "narrator_chain": "", "chapter_intro": "Speech"}
{"hadithnumber": "1948", "arabic": "حَدَّثَنِي مَالِكٌ، عَنْ زَيْدِ بْنِ أَسْلَمَ، عَنْ عَطَاءِ بْنِ يَسَارٍ، أَنَّ رَسُولَ اللَّهِ صلى الله عليه وسلم قَالَ ‏\"‏ مَنْ وَقَاهُ اللَّهُ شَرَّ اثْنَيْنِ وَلَجَ الْجَنَّةَ ‏\"‏ ‏.‏ فَقَالَ رَجُلٌ يَا رَسُولَ اللَّهِ لاَ تُخْبِرْنَا ‏.‏ فَسَكَتَ رَسُولُ اللَّهِ صلى الله عليه وسلم ثُمَّ عَادَ رَسُولُ اللَّهِ صلى الله عليه وسلم فَقَالَ مِثْلَ مَقَالَتِهِ الأُولَى فَقَالَ لَهُ الرَّجُلُ لاَ تُخْبِرْنَا يَا رَسُولَ اللَّهِ ‏.‏ فَسَكَتَ رَسُولُ اللَّهِ صلى الله عليه وسلم ثُمَّ قَالَ رَسُولُ اللَّهِ صلى الله عليه وسلم مِثْلَ ذَلِكَ أَيْضًا فَقَالَ الرَّجُلُ لاَ تُخْبِرْنَا يَا رَسُولَ اللَّهِ ‏.‏ ثُمَّ قَالَ رَسُولُ اللَّهِ صلى الله عليه وسلم مِثْلَ ذَلِكَ أَيْضًا ‏.‏ ثُمَّ ذَهَبَ الرَّجُلُ يَقُولُ مِثْلَ مَقَالَتِهِ الأُولَى فَأَسْكَتَهُ رَجُلٌ إِلَى جَنْبِهِ ‏.‏ فَقَالَ رَسُولُ اللَّهِ صلى الله عليه وسلم ‏\"‏ مَنْ وَقَاهُ اللَّهُ شَرَّ اثْنَيْنِ وَلَجَ الْجَنَّةَ مَا بَيْنَ لَحْيَيْهِ وَمَا بَيْنَ رِجْلَيْهِ مَا بَيْنَ لَحْيَيْهِ وَمَا بَيْنَ رِجْلَيْهِ مَا بَيْنَ لَحْيَيْهِ وَمَا بَيْنَ رِجْلَيْهِ ‏\"‏ ‏.‏", "bengali": "", "english": "Malik related to me from Zayd ibn Aslam from Ata ibn Yasar that the Messenger of Allah, may Allah bless him and grant him peace, said, \"Whomever Allah protects from the evil of two things will enter the Garden.\" A man said, \"Messenger of Allah, do not tell us!\" The Messenger of Allah, may Allah bless him and grant him peace, was silent. Then the Messenger of Allah, may Allah bless him and grant him peace, repeated what he had said the first time. The man said to him, \"Do not tell us, Messenger of Allah!\" The Messenger of Allah, may Allah bless him and grant him peace, was silent. Then the Messenger of Allah, may Allah bless him and grant him peace, said the same thing again. The man said, \"Do not tell us, Messenger of Allah!\" Then the Messenger of Allah, may Allah bless him and grant him peace, said the same thing again. Then the man began to say what he had said previously and a man at his side silenced him. The Messenger of Allah, may Allah bless him and grant him peace, said, \"Whomever Allah protects from the evil of two things will enter the Garden. They are what is between his jaws and what is between his legs, what is between his jaws and what is between his legs, what is between his jaws and what is between his legs.\"", "french": "", "indonesian": "", "russian": "", "urdu": "", "grades": "", "reference": "", "international_number": "", "narrator_chain": "", "chapter_intro": "Speech"}
{"hadithnumber": "1949", "arabic": "وَحَدَّثَنِي مَالِكٌ، عَنْ زَيْدِ بْنِ أَسْلَمَ، عَنْ أَبِيهِ، أَنَّ عُمَرَ بْنَ الْخَطَّابِ، دَخَلَ عَلَى أَبِي بَكْرٍ الصِّدِّيقِ وَهُوَ يَجْبِذُ لِسَانَهُ فَقَالَ لَهُ عُمَرُ مَهْ غَفَرَ اللَّهُ لَكَ ‏.‏ فَقَالَ أَبُو بَكْرٍ إِنَّ هَذَا أَوْرَدَنِي الْمَوَارِدَ ‏.‏", "bengali": "", "english": "Malik related to me from Zayd ibn Aslam from his father that Umar ibn al-Khattab came upon Abu Bakr as-Siddiq pulling his tongue. Umar said to him, \"Stop, may Allah forgive you!\" Abu Bakr replied, \"This has brought me to dangerous places.\"", "french": "", "indonesian": "", "russian": "", "urdu": "", "grades": "", "reference": "", "international_number": "", "narrator_chain": "", "chapter_intro": "Speech"}
{"hadithnumber": "1950", "arabic": "وَحَدَّثَنِي مَالِكٌ، عَنْ عَبْدِ اللَّهِ بْنِ دِينَارٍ، قَالَ كُنْتُ أَنَا وَعَبْدُ اللَّهِ بْنُ عُمَرَ، عِنْدَ دَارِ خَالِدِ بْنِ عُقْبَةَ الَّتِي بِالسُّوقِ فَجَاءَ رَجُلٌ يُرِيدُ أَنْ يُنَاجِيَهُ وَلَيْسَ مَعَ عَبْدِ اللَّهِ بْنِ عُمَرَ أَحَدٌ غَيْرِي وَغَيْرُ الرَّجُلِ الَّذِي يُرِيدُ أَنْ يُنَاجِيَهُ فَدَعَا عَبْدُ اللَّهِ بْنُ عُمَرَ رَجُلاً آخَرَ حَتَّى كُنَّا أَرْبَعَةً فَقَالَ لِي وَلِلرَّجُلِ الَّذِي دَعَاهُ اسْتَأْخِرَا شَيْئًا فَإِنِّي سَمِعْتُ رَسُولَ اللَّهِ صلى الله عليه وسلم يَقُولُ ‏ ‏ لاَ يَتَنَاجَى اثْنَانِ دُونَ وَاحِدٍ ‏\"\"‏ ‏.‏\"", "bengali": "", "english": "Malik related to me from Abdullah ibn Dinar saying, \"Abdullah ibn Umar and I were at the house of Khalid ibn Uqba who was away at the market. A man came who wanted to speak to Abdullah ibn Umar and I was the only other person present Abdullah ibn Umar called another man so that we were four and said to me and the man whom he had called, 'Go a little way off together, because I heard the Messenger of Allah, may Allah bless him and grant him peace, say, \"Two do not converse secretly to the exclusion of another.' \"'", "french": "", "indonesian": "", "russian": "", "urdu": "", "grades": "", "reference": "", "international_number": "", "narrator_chain": "", "chapter_intro": "Speech"}
{"hadithnumber": "1951", "arabic": "وَحَدَّثَنِي مَالِكٌ، عَنْ نَافِعٍ، عَنْ عَبْدِ اللَّهِ بْنِ عُمَرَ، أَنَّ رَسُولَ اللَّهِ صلى الله عليه وسلم قَالَ ‏ ‏ إِذَا كَانَ ثَلاَثَةٌ فَلاَ يَتَنَاجَى اثْنَانِ دُونَ وَاحِدٍ ‏\"\"‏ ‏.‏\"", "bengali": "", "english": "Malik related to me from Nafi from Abdullah ibn Umar that the Messenger of Allah, may Allah bless him and grant him peace, said, \"Two must not converse secretly to the exclusion of another person.\"", "french": "", "indonesian": "", "russian": "", "urdu": "", "grades": "", "reference": "", "international_number": "", "narrator_chain": "", "chapter_intro": "Speech"}
{"hadithnumber": "1952", "arabic": "حَدَّثَنِي مَالِكٌ، عَنْ صَفْوَانَ بْنِ سُلَيْمٍ، أَنَّ رَجُلاً، قَالَ لِرَسُولِ اللَّهِ صلى الله عليه وسلم أَكْذِبُ امْرَأَتِي يَا رَسُولَ اللَّهِ فَقَالَ رَسُولُ اللَّهِ صلى الله عليه وسلم ‏\"‏ لاَ خَيْرَ فِي الْكَذِبِ ‏\"‏ ‏.‏ فَقَالَ الرَّجُلُ يَا رَسُولَ اللَّهِ أَعِدُهَا وَأَقُولُ لَهَا فَقَالَ رَسُولُ اللَّهِ صلى الله عليه وسلم ‏\"‏ لاَ جُنَاحَ عَلَيْكَ ‏\"‏ ‏.‏", "bengali": "", "english": "Malik related to me from Safwan ibn Sulaym that a man asked the Messenger of Allah, may Allah bless him and grant him peace, \"Can I lie to my wife, Messenger of Allah?\" The Messenger of Allah, may Allah bless him and grant him peace, said, \"There is no good in lying.\" The man said, \"Messenger of Allah! Shall I make her a promise and tell her?\" The Messenger of Allah, may Allah bless him and grant him peace, said, \"It will not be held against you.\"", "french": "", "indonesian": "", "russian": "", "urdu": "", "grades": "", "reference": "", "international_number": "", "narrator_chain": "", "chapter_intro": "Speech"}
{"hadithnumber": "1953", "arabic": "وَحَدَّثَنِي مَالِكٌ، أَنَّهُ بَلَغَهُ أَنَّ عَبْدَ اللَّهِ بْنَ مَسْعُودٍ، كَانَ يَقُولُ عَلَيْكُمْ بِالصِّدْقِ فَإِنَّ الصِّدْقَ يَهْدِي إِلَى الْبِرِّ وَالْبِرَّ يَهْدِي إِلَى الْجَنَّةِ وَإِيَّاكُمْ وَالْكَذِبَ فَإِنَّ الْكَذِبَ يَهْدِي إِلَى الْفُجُورِ وَالْفُجُورَ يَهْدِي إِلَى النَّارِ أَلاَ تَرَى أَنَّهُ يُقَالُ صَدَقَ وَبَرَّ وَكَذَبَ وَفَجَرَ ‏.‏", "bengali": "", "english": "Malik related to me that he heard that Abdullah ibn Masud used to say, \"You must tell the truth. Truthfulness leads to right action. Right action leads to the Garden. Beware of lying. Lying leads to corruption, and corruption leads to the Fire. Don't you see that it is said, 'He speaks the truth and acts rightly,' and, 'He lies and is corrupt.' \"", "french": "", "indonesian": "", "russian": "", "urdu": "", "grades": "", "reference": "", "international_number": "", "narrator_chain": "", "chapter_intro": "Speech"}
{"hadithnumber": "1954", "arabic": "وَحَدَّثَنِي مَالِكٌ، أَنَّهُ بَلَغَهُ أَنَّهُ قِيلَ لِلُقْمَانَ مَا بَلَغَ بِكَ مَا نَرَى يُرِيدُونَ الْفَضْلَ ‏.‏ فَقَالَ لُقْمَانُ صِدْقُ الْحَدِيثِ وَأَدَاءُ الأَمَانَةِ وَتَرْكُ مَا لاَ يَعْنِينِي ‏.‏", "bengali": "", "english": "Malik related to me that he heard that someone said to Luqman, \"What has brought you to what we see?\" meaning his high rank. Luqman said, \"Truthful speech, fulfilling the trust, and leaving what does not concern me.\"", "french": "", "indonesian": "", "russian": "", "urdu": "", "grades": "", "reference": "", "international_number": "", "narrator_chain": "", "chapter_intro": "Speech"}
{"hadithnumber": "1955", "arabic": "وَحَدَّثَنِي مَالِكٌ، أَنَّهُ بَلَغَهُ أَنَّ عَبْدَ اللَّهِ بْنَ مَسْعُودٍ، كَانَ يَقُولُ لاَ يَزَالُ الْعَبْدُ يَكْذِبُ وَتُنْكَتُ فِي قَلْبِهِ نُكْتَةٌ سَوْدَاءُ حَتَّى يَسْوَدَّ قَلْبُهُ كُلُّهُ فَيُكْتَبَ عِنْدَ اللَّهِ مِنَ الْكَاذِبِينَ ‏.‏", "bengali": "", "english": "Malik related to me that he heard that Abdullah ibn Masud used to say, \"The slave continues to lie and a black spot grows in his heart until all his heart becomes black. Then he is written, in Allah's sight, among the liars.\"", "french": "", "indonesian": "", "russian": "", "urdu": "", "grades": "", "reference": "", "international_number": "", "narrator_chain": "", "chapter_intro": "Speech"}
{"hadithnumber": "1956", "arabic": "وَحَدَّثَنِي مَالِكٌ، عَنْ صَفْوَانَ بْنِ سُلَيْمٍ، أَنَّهُ قَالَ قِيلَ لِرَسُولِ اللَّهِ صلى الله عليه وسلم أَيَكُونُ الْمُؤْمِنُ جَبَانًا فَقَالَ ‏\"‏ نَعَمْ ‏\"‏ ‏.‏ فَقِيلَ لَهُ أَيَكُونُ الْمُؤْمِنُ بَخِيلاً فَقَالَ ‏\"‏ نَعَمْ ‏\"‏ ‏.‏ فَقِيلَ لَهُ أَيَكُونُ الْمُؤْمِنُ كَذَّابًا فَقَالَ ‏\"‏ لاَ ‏\"‏ ‏.‏", "bengali": "", "english": "Malik related to me that Safwan ibn Sulaym said, \"The Messenger of Allah, may Allah bless him and grant him peace, was asked, 'Can the mumin be a coward?' He said, 'Yes.' He was asked, 'Can the mumin be a miser?' He said, 'Yes.' He was asked, 'Can the mumin be a liar?' He said, 'No.' \"", "french": "", "indonesian": "", "russian": "", "urdu": "", "grades": "", "reference": "", "international_number": "", "narrator_chain": "", "chapter_intro": "Speech"}
{"hadithnumber": "1957", "arabic": "حَدَّثَنِي مَالِكٌ، عَنْ سُهَيْلِ بْنِ أَبِي صَالِحٍ، عَنْ أَبِيهِ، عَنْ أَبِي هُرَيْرَةَ، أَنَّ رَسُولَ اللَّهِ صلى الله عليه وسلم قَالَ ‏ ‏ إِنَّ اللَّهَ يَرْضَى لَكُمْ ثَلاَثًا وَيَسْخَطُ لَكُمْ ثَلاَثًا يَرْضَى لَكُمْ أَنْ تَعْبُدُوهُ وَلاَ تُشْرِكُوا بِهِ شَيْئًا وَأَنْ تَعْتَصِمُوا بِحَبْلِ اللَّهِ جَمِيعًا وَأَنْ تَنَاصَحُوا مَنْ وَلاَّهُ اللَّهُ أَمْرَكُمْ وَيَسْخَطُ لَكُمْ قِيلَ وَقَالَ وَإِضَاعَةَ الْمَالِ وَكَثْرَةَ السُّؤَالِ ‏\"\"‏ ‏.‏\"", "bengali": "", "english": "Malik related to me from Suhayl ibn Abi Salih from his father from Abu Hurayra that the Messenger of Allah, may Allah bless him and grant him peace, said, \"Allah is pleased with three things from you, and He is angry with three things from you. He is pleased that you worship Him and do not associate anything with Him, and that you take hold of the rope of Allah altogether, and that you give good counsel to the one to whom Allah gives command over you. He is angry with you for gossip, squandering property, and asking too many questions.\"", "french": "", "indonesian": "", "russian": "", "urdu": "", "grades": "", "reference": "", "international_number": "", "narrator_chain": "", "chapter_intro": "Speech"}
{"hadithnumber": "1958", "arabic": "وَحَدَّثَنِي مَالِكٌ، عَنْ أَبِي الزِّنَادِ، عَنِ الأَعْرَجِ، عَنْ أَبِي هُرَيْرَةَ، أَنَّ رَسُولَ اللَّهِ صلى الله عليه وسلم قَالَ ‏ ‏ مِنْ شَرِّ النَّاسِ ذُو الْوَجْهَيْنِ الَّذِي يَأْتِي هَؤُلاَءِ بِوَجْهٍ وَهَؤُلاَءِ بِوَجْهٍ ‏\"\"‏ ‏.‏\"", "bengali": "", "english": "Malik related to me from Abu'z-Zinad from al-Araj from Abu Hurayra that the Messenger of Allah, may Allah bless him and grant him peace, said, \"One of the most evil of people is the two-faced person who shows one face to these people and another face to those people.\"", "french": "", "indonesian": "", "russian": "", "urdu": "", "grades": "", "reference": "", "international_number": "", "narrator_chain": "", "chapter_intro": "Speech"}
{"hadithnumber": "1959", "arabic": "حَدَّثَنِي مَالِكٌ، أَنَّهُ بَلَغَهُ أَنَّ أُمَّ سَلَمَةَ، زَوْجَ النَّبِيِّ صلى الله عليه وسلم قَالَتْ يَا رَسُولَ اللَّهِ أَنَهْلِكُ وَفِينَا الصَّالِحُونَ فَقَالَ رَسُولُ اللَّهِ صلى الله عليه وسلم ‏ ‏ نَعَمْ إِذَا كَثُرَ الْخَبَثُ ‏\"\"‏ ‏.‏\"", "bengali": "", "english": "Malik related to me that he had heard that Umm Salama, the wife of the Prophet, may Allah bless him and grant him peace, said, \"Messenger of Allah! Shall we be destroyed while there are people who are salih among us?\" The Messenger of Allah, may Allah bless him and grant him peace, said, \"Yes, if there is much wickedness.\"", "french": "", "indonesian": "", "russian": "", "urdu": "", "grades": "", "reference": "", "international_number": "", "narrator_chain": "", "chapter_intro": "Speech"}
{"hadithnumber": "1960", "arabic": "وَحَدَّثَنِي مَالِكٌ، عَنْ إِسْمَاعِيلَ بْنِ أَبِي حَكِيمٍ، أَنَّهُ سَمِعَ عُمَرَ بْنَ عَبْدِ الْعَزِيزِ، يَقُولُ كَانَ يُقَالُ إِنَّ اللَّهَ تَبَارَكَ وَتَعَالَى لاَ يُعَذِّبُ الْعَامَّةَ بِذَنْبِ الْخَاصَّةِ وَلَكِنْ إِذَا عُمِلَ الْمُنْكَرُ جِهَارًا اسْتَحَقُّوا الْعُقُوبَةَ كُلُّهُمْ ‏.‏", "bengali": "", "english": "Malik related to me that Ismail ibn Abi Hakim heard Umar ibn Abd al-Aziz say, \"Some say that Allah the Blessed, the Exalted, will not punish the many for the wrong action of the few. However, when the objectionable action is committed openly, then they all deserve to be punished.\"", "french": "", "indonesian": "", "russian": "", "urdu": "", "grades": "", "reference": "", "international_number": "", "narrator_chain": "", "chapter_intro": "Speech"}
{"hadithnumber": "1961", "arabic": "حَدَّثَنِي مَالِكٌ، عَنْ إِسْحَاقَ بْنِ عَبْدِ اللَّهِ بْنِ أَبِي طَلْحَةَ، عَنْ أَنَسِ بْنِ مَالِكٍ، قَالَ سَمِعْتُ عُمَرَ بْنَ الْخَطَّابِ، وَخَرَجْتُ، مَعَهُ حَتَّى دَخَلَ حَائِطًا فَسَمِعْتُهُ وَهُوَ، يَقُولُ وَبَيْنِي وَبَيْنَهُ جِدَارٌ - وَهُوَ فِي جَوْفِ الْحَائِطِ - عُمَرُ بْنُ الْخَطَّابِ أَمِيرُ الْمُؤْمِنِينَ بَخٍ بَخٍ وَاللَّهِ لَتَتَّقِيَنَّ اللَّهَ أَوْ لَيُعَذِّبَنَّكَ ‏.‏", "bengali": "", "english": "Malik related to me from Ishaq ibn Abdullah ibn Abi Talha that Anas ibn Malik said, \"I heard Umar ibn al-Khattab, when I was going out with him to visit an orchard, say to himself, and there was a wall between him and me and he was inside the garden, 'Umar ibn al-Khattab, amir al-muminin! Well done! Well done! By Allah, fear Allah or he will punish you.' \"", "french": "", "indonesian": "", "russian": "", "urdu": "", "grades": "", "reference": "", "international_number": "", "narrator_chain": "", "chapter_intro": "Speech"}
{"hadithnumber": "1962", "arabic": "قَالَ مَالِكٌ وَبَلَغَنِي أَنَّ الْقَاسِمَ بْنَ مُحَمَّدٍ كَانَ يَقُولُ أَدْرَكْتُ النَّاسَ وَمَا يَعْجَبُونَ بِالْقَوْلِ ‏.‏ قَالَ مَالِكٌ يُرِيدُ بِذَلِكَ الْعَمَلَ إِنَّمَا يُنْظَرُ إِلَى عَمَلِهِ وَلاَ يُنْظَرُ إِلَى قَوْلِهِ ‏.‏", "bengali": "", "english": "Malik said, \"I heard that al-Qasim ibn Muhammad used to say, 'I have seen the people, (i.e. the companions), and they were not impressed by speech.' \" Malik said, \"He meant that only action and deeds would be looked at, not words.\"", "french": "", "indonesian": "", "russian": "", "urdu": "", "grades": "", "reference": "", "international_number": "", "narrator_chain": "", "chapter_intro": "Speech"}
{"hadithnumber": "1963", "arabic": "حَدَّثَنِي مَالِكٌ، عَنْ عَامِرِ بْنِ عَبْدِ اللَّهِ بْنِ الزُّبَيْرِ، أَنَّهُ كَانَ إِذَا سَمِعَ الرَّعْدَ، تَرَكَ الْحَدِيثَ", "bengali": "", "english": "Malik related to me that Amir ibn Abdullah ibn az-Zubayr would stop speaking when he heard thunder and say, \"Glory be to Allah whom the thunder glorifies with His praise and the angels from the fear of Him.\" (Subhana-aladhee yusabihu ar-radu bi hamdihi wa mala'ikatu min khiyfatihi.) Then he would say, \"This is a severe warning to the people of the earth.\"", "french": "", "indonesian": "", "russian": "", "urdu": "", "grades": "", "reference": "", "international_number": "", "narrator_chain": "", "chapter_intro": "Speech"}
{"hadithnumber": "1964", "arabic": "حَدَّثَنِي مَالِكٌ، عَنِ ابْنِ شِهَابٍ، عَنْ عُرْوَةَ بْنِ الزُّبَيْرِ، عَنْ عَائِشَةَ أُمِّ الْمُؤْمِنِينَ، أَنَّ أَزْوَاجَ النَّبِيِّ، صلى الله عليه وسلم حِينَ تُوُفِّيَ رَسُولُ اللَّهِ صلى الله عليه وسلم أَرَدْنَ أَنْ يَبْعَثْنَ عُثْمَانَ بْنَ عَفَّانَ إِلَى أَبِي بَكْرٍ الصِّدِّيقِ فَيَسْأَلْنَهُ مِيرَاثَهُنَّ مِنْ رَسُولِ اللَّهِ صلى الله عليه وسلم فَقَالَتْ لَهُنَّ عَائِشَةُ أَلَيْسَ قَدْ قَالَ رَسُولُ اللَّهِ صلى الله عليه وسلم ‏ ‏ لاَ نُورَثُ مَا تَرَكْنَا فَهُوَ صَدَقَةٌ ‏\"\"‏ ‏.‏\"", "bengali": "", "english": "Malik related to me from Ibn Shihab from Urwa ibn az-Zubayr from A'isha, umm al-muminin that when the Messenger of Allah, may Allah bless him and grant him peace, died, the wives of the Prophet, may Allah bless him and grant him peace, wanted to send Uthman ibn Affan to Abu Bakr as-Siddiq to ask him about their inheritance from the Messenger of Allah, may Allah bless him and grant him peace A'isha said to them, \"Didn't the Messenger of Allah, may Allah bless him and grant him peace, say, 'No one inherits from us. What we leave is sadaqa.' \"", "french": "", "indonesian": "", "russian": "", "urdu": "", "grades": "", "reference": "", "international_number": "", "narrator_chain": "", "chapter_intro": "Speech"}
{"hadithnumber": "1965", "arabic": "وَحَدَّثَنِي مَالِكٌ، عَنْ أَبِي الزِّنَادِ، عَنِ الأَعْرَجِ، عَنْ أَبِي هُرَيْرَةَ، أَنَّ رَسُولَ اللَّهِ صلى الله عليه وسلم قَالَ ‏ ‏ لاَ يَقْتَسِمُ وَرَثَتِي دَنَانِيرَ مَا تَرَكْتُ بَعْدَ نَفَقَةِ نِسَائِي وَمُؤْنَةِ عَامِلِي فَهُوَ صَدَقَةٌ ‏\"\"‏ ‏.‏\"", "bengali": "", "english": "Malik related to me from Abu'z-Zinad from al-Araj from Abu Hurayra that the Messenger of Allah, may Allah bless him and grant him peace, said, \"My inheritance is not divided up by the dinar. What I leave apart from the maintenance of my wives and provision for my servant is sadaqa.\"", "french": "", "indonesian": "", "russian": "", "urdu": "", "grades": "", "reference": "", "international_number": "", "narrator_chain": "", "chapter_intro": "Speech"}
